    "title": "Preparing views for localization"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Localize SwiftUI views so users experience your app in their own native",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "language, region, and culture.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Xcode parses SwiftUI views for strings to localize when exporting a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "localization catalog. You can add hints so that Xcode generates correct,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "hinted strings to localize for your app.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For information about string catalogs, see",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Xcode/localizing-and-varying-text-with-a-string-catalog",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Add-comments-to-text-views",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Add comments to text views",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To ease the translation process, provide hints to translators that share",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "how and where your app displays the strings of a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Text",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " view.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "To add a hint, use the optional ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "comment",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter to the text view",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "initializer ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Text/init(_:tableName:bundle:comment:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "When you localize your app with Xcode, it includes the comment string",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "along with the string. For example, the following text view includes a comment:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "Text(\"Explore\",",
            "     comment: \"The title of the tab bar item that navigates to the Explore screen.\")"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Xcode creates the following entry in your string catalog file for this view:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "Preparing-views-for-localization-1",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Provide-additional-information-with-text-views",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Provide additional information with text views",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can localize many SwiftUI views that have a string label",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "by providing a string that SwiftUI interprets as a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/LocalizedStringKey",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The system uses the key to retrieve a localized value from your string",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "catalog at runtime, or uses the string directly if it can’t find",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the key in the catalog. For example, SwiftUI uses the string input to the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "following ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Label",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " initializer as a localized string key:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "Label(\"Message\", image: \"msgSymbol\")"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you additionally want to provide a comment for localization, you can",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "use an explicit ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Text",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " view instead:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "Label {",
            "    Text(\"Message\",",
            "         comment: \"A label that displays 'Message' and a corresponding image.\")",
            "} icon: {",
            "    Image(\"msgSymbol\")",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Many SwiftUI controls have view builder initializers that enable you to follow",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "this pattern. For more information on how to make your app’s text translatable,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Xcode/preparing-your-apps-text-for-translation",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
